Project Dependency Graph

Dependency Tree

  • net.automatalib:automata-misc-algorithms:jar:0.5.1
    AutomataLib :: Misc :: Misc. Algorithms

    Description: This artifact contains several miscellaneous, well-known algorithms, which however are rather specific in their concrete use case and therefore not fit for the AutomataLib Utilities library. Examples include Dijkstra's algorithm for the SSSP problem, the Floyd-Warshall algorithm for the APSP problem and Tarjan's algorithm for finding all strongly-connected components in a graph.

    URL: http://misberner.github.io/automatalib/maven-site/0.5.1/automata-misc-parent/automata-misc-algorithms

    Project License: GNU LESSER GENERAL PUBLIC LICENSE Version 3, 29 June 2007

        URL: http://code.google.com/p/guava-libraries/guava

        Project License: The Apache Software License, Version 2.0

    • net.automatalib:automata-commons-smartcollections:jar:0.5.1 (compile)
      AutomataLib :: Commons :: Smart Collections

      Description: This library provides efficient implementations for various collection data structures (esp. linked lists and priority queues), which have very insufficient implementation in the Java Collections Foundations that makes it hard or even impossible to exploit their efficiencies.

      URL: http://misberner.github.io/automatalib/maven-site/0.5.1/automata-commons-parent/automata-commons-smartcollections

      Project License: GNU LESSER GENERAL PUBLIC LICENSE Version 3, 29 June 2007

    • net.automatalib:automata-api:jar:0.5.1 (compile)
      AutomataLib :: API

      Description: This artifact contains the API of AutomataLib, which mainly consists of interfaces for the various concepts and automaton models supported by the AutomataLib core. In addition to that, it also defines some fundamental classes for dealing with words of symbols.

      URL: http://misberner.github.io/automatalib/maven-site/0.5.1/automata-api

      Project License: GNU LESSER GENERAL PUBLIC LICENSE Version 3, 29 June 2007

    • net.automatalib:automata-core:jar:0.5.1 (compile)
      AutomataLib :: Core

      Description: The core artifact of AutomataLib. This library contains concrete implementations for many of the automaton model interfaces defined in the API artifact, as well as abstract base classes that facilitate implementing new automaton model classes. Note that concrete algorithms (traversal, reachability analysis etc.) are not in the scope of this artifact.

      URL: http://misberner.github.io/automatalib/maven-site/0.5.1/automata-core

      Project License: GNU LESSER GENERAL PUBLIC LICENSE Version 3, 29 June 2007

      • net.sf.trove4j:trove4j:jar:3.0.3 (compile)
        GNU Trove

        Description: The Trove library provides high speed regular and primitive collections for Java.

        URL: http://trove4j.sf.net

        Project License: GNU Lesser General Public License 2.1

    • net.automatalib:automata-util:jar:0.5.1 (compile)
      AutomataLib :: Utilities

      Description: This artifact provides various common utility operations for analyzing and manipulating automata and graphs, such as traversal, minimization and copying.

      URL: http://misberner.github.io/automatalib/maven-site/0.5.1/automata-util

      Project License: GNU LESSER GENERAL PUBLIC LICENSE Version 3, 29 June 2007

      • net.automatalib:automata-commons-dotutil:jar:0.5.1 (compile)
        AutomataLib :: Commons :: DOT Utilities

        Description: This utility artifact contains methods that facilitate interaction with the <a href="http://www.graphviz.org/">GraphVIZ DOT</a> tool, and allows to render and display DOT models directly from within the application.

        URL: http://misberner.github.io/automatalib/maven-site/0.5.1/automata-commons-parent/automata-commons-dotutil

        Project License: GNU LESSER GENERAL PUBLIC LICENSE Version 3, 29 June 2007
